Definition: the solar calendar now in general use, introduced by Gregory XIII in 1582 to correct an error in the Julian calendar by suppressing 10 days, making Oct 5 be called Oct 15, and providing that only centenary years divisible by 400 should be leap years
Example: it was adopted by Great Britain and the American colonies in 1752
Synonyms: New_Style_calendar, solar_calendar, the, solar, calendar, now, in, general, use, introduced, by, Gregory, XIII, to, correct, an, error, Julian, suppressing, days, making, Oct, be, called, and, providing, that, only, centenary, years, divisible, should, leap, it, was, adopted, Great, Britain, American, colonies
Category: noun.time
